        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28899",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=miallen",
                        "name": "miallen",
                        "displayName": "Michael B Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "An email address is not a qualified account name. It is just an email address. What you want is basically ACCTNAME_FORM_EMAIL = 5 with corresponding logic to canonicalize the account name to the mail attribute. Which is to say Zend_Auth_Adapter_Ldap simply does not implement this.\n\nNote that I think this would require querying the LDAP server which would slow things down a little.\n\nI agree this should be implemented but I will not be active on this project for the foreseeable future.\n\nYou could extend Zend_Ldap to add the desired behavior (and then you would have to also extend Zend_Auth_Adapter_Ldap so that it used your extended Zend_Ldap).\n\nFinally, this should really be assigned to Zend_Ldap and not Zend_Auth_Adapter_Ldap as Zend_Ldap is where the actual name canonicalization occurs.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=miallen",
                        "name": "miallen",
                        "displayName": "Michael B Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-02-17T13:16:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-02-17T13:16:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28909",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The new extended Zend_Ldap component that currently is in the Standard Incubator takes care of this issue as it provides a '{{tryUsernameSplit}}' option that, when set to {{false}}, will skip the splitting operation you described in case (2) and will allow to pass the full email address to the LDAP server. (I admit that the option name is not quite perfect yet...)\n\nPerhaps you can try the new component or extract the relevant code to extend Zend_Ldap yourself as Michael pointed out.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-02-17T23:52:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-02-17T23:52:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32740",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "fixed in trunk for next minor-release 1.9. Behaviour is controlled by the option key tryUsernameSplit,",
                    "updateAuthor": {
